wikipedia_page.main: Jeannie Robertson (1908 – 13 March 1975) was a Scottish folk singer.Her most celebrated song is "I'm a Man You Don't Meet Every Day", otherwise known as "Jock Stewart". It has been recorded by Archie Fisher, The Dubliners, The McCalmans, The Tannahill Weavers and The Pogues. Variants are known from the US in the 1880s and Australia in the 1850s.
